00:40:00,400 --> 00:40:01,400
 says.

688
00:40:01,400 --> 00:40:02,400
 There is freedom there.

689
00:40:02,400 --> 00:40:05,040
 He says they will be blessed in what they do.

690
00:40:05,040 --> 00:40:06,960
 There is blessing in the doing.

691
00:40:06,960 --> 00:40:13,200
 God is trying to bless you through his word, and that's good news.

692
00:40:13,200 --> 00:40:16,960
 The last thing that I'll say is this.

693
00:40:16,960 --> 00:40:22,000
 I mean it when I say the goal of the Bible, showing us ourselves, is not for us to be

694
00:40:22,000 --> 00:40:24,800
 overcome with guilt and shame.

695
00:40:24,800 --> 00:40:27,520
 If we're guilty, then it's okay to acknowledge that.

696
00:40:27,520 --> 00:40:37,320
 It's a good thing, but one of the things that we see so clearly in Scripture is that Jesus

697
00:40:37,320 --> 00:40:40,280
 is the only one who has ever kept the law perfectly.

698
00:40:40,280 --> 00:40:45,480
 You know what's incredible about Jesus, Jesus doesn't say, "Oh, usually I do the will of

699
00:40:45,480 --> 00:40:47,280
 the Father, usually I do the right thing."

700
00:40:47,280 --> 00:40:53,320
 Jesus says, "I always do the will of the Father, I always do the will of the Father," and the

701
00:40:53,320 --> 00:40:59,640
 incredible thing about the gospel of Jesus is that God has said, "I know that y'all have

702
00:40:59,640 --> 00:41:00,960
 not kept the law perfectly."

703
00:41:00,960 --> 00:41:04,360
 If you're here today and you say, "Well, look, if what it takes for me to follow Jesus is

704
00:41:04,360 --> 00:41:09,400
 I have to keep the law, I have to keep it perfectly," actually what the Bible says is

705
00:41:09,400 --> 00:41:10,400
 this.

706
00:41:10,400 --> 00:41:14,720
 You haven't kept the law perfectly, so Jesus came and he did it for you.

707
00:41:14,720 --> 00:41:19,560
 The mistake that we make is we think, "I have to do all the good things, I have to obey

708
00:41:19,560 --> 00:41:23,640
 so that I can make it into God's love, so that God will love me, so that I can belong,"

709
00:41:23,640 --> 00:41:25,920
 and this is what happens in every single area of our life.

710
00:41:25,920 --> 00:41:29,000
 This is what happens with college, this is what happens with work, this is what happens

711
00:41:29,000 --> 00:41:31,720
 with friend groups, this is what happens with clubs we want to be in.

712
00:41:31,720 --> 00:41:35,360
 Everybody's like, "Well, just show me you're worthy, show me your resume, show me what

713
00:41:35,360 --> 00:41:40,100
 you like, show me what you've done, impress me."

714
00:41:40,100 --> 00:41:43,600
 We spend so much of our lives trying to impress and now we think, "Now I got to come to God

715
00:41:43,600 --> 00:41:46,640
 and I got to do all the right stuff so that God will love me."

716
00:41:46,640 --> 00:41:50,440
 What the Bible says is that God already loves you.

717
00:41:50,440 --> 00:41:54,680
 What the Bible says is actually Jesus already said you can't do it perfectly, so he did

718
00:41:54,680 --> 00:41:56,720
 it for you.

719
00:41:56,720 --> 00:42:04,480
 This is the difference between my son wanting to obey me and if he was like, "Dad, I want

720
00:42:04,480 --> 00:42:07,600
 to do what you said because I know if I don't you're going to kick me out the house."

721
00:42:07,600 --> 00:42:12,640
 I don't know, my son understands that when I ask him to do something, the only thing

722
00:42:12,640 --> 00:42:15,720
 it would cause in our relationship is for me to call him to something better.

723
00:42:15,720 --> 00:42:17,160
 He's not getting kicked out the house.

724
00:42:17,160 --> 00:42:21,280
 What Jesus is saying is, "I'm not telling you to obey, to earn your way in the house,

725
00:42:21,280 --> 00:42:25,480
 I've already done that for you, come in the house.

726
00:42:25,480 --> 00:42:28,400
 And then once you get in here, let me show you a better way."

727
00:42:28,400 --> 00:42:30,760
 Jesus in his word has shown us a better way.

728
00:42:30,760 --> 00:42:34,320
 If you're here today and you don't know Jesus, I want you to know Jesus is not trying to

729
00:42:34,320 --> 00:42:36,760
 put burdens on you, he's trying to take burdens off.

730
00:42:36,760 --> 00:42:40,880
 Jesus is not trying to put handcuffs on you, he's trying to take handcuffs off and he loves

731
00:42:40,880 --> 00:42:46,200
 us so much that he gave his life to do it.

732
00:42:46,200 --> 00:42:54,060
 What a great love.

733
00:42:54,060 --> 00:42:58,640
 And so as he welcomes us in by faith, putting our faith in Jesus is how we get into the

734
00:42:58,640 --> 00:43:04,400
 family and he says, "Let me guide you in the right direction."

735
00:43:04,400 --> 00:43:09,980
 My prayer is that you would hear God's word, you would receive it, you would remove the

736
00:43:09,980 --> 00:43:13,600
 things that block it, and that by God's grace, we would respond.

737
00:43:13,600 --> 00:43:14,880
 Let's pray.

738
00:43:14,880 --> 00:43:19,920
 Father, we come before you in Jesus' name, Lord, and we thank you for your word.

739
00:43:19,920 --> 00:43:23,280
 We thank you for speaking to us, God, and we thank you for speaking to us tonight.

740
00:43:23,280 --> 00:43:28,360
 And God, we pray that even now you would keep us from anything that would distract us from

741
00:43:28,360 --> 00:43:30,000
 remembering what you've had to say.

742
00:43:30,000 --> 00:43:33,400
 God, I pray the conversations we have after this will be conversations that would help

743
00:43:33,400 --> 00:43:37,840
 us to remember, Lord, and help us to serve and love one another in that.

744
00:43:37,840 --> 00:43:41,920
 And I pray for my brothers and sisters in the room who maybe feel guilt about not obeying

745
00:43:41,920 --> 00:43:45,800
 you perfectly, that they would remember that the same place they ran to to connect with

746
00:43:45,800 --> 00:43:49,300
 you the first time, to have relationship with you, the cross of Jesus is the same place

747
00:43:49,300 --> 00:43:52,060
 you called them to now.

748
00:43:52,060 --> 00:43:57,040
 And you call us to freedom, God, and we pray that you'd help us to walk in it.

749
00:43:57,040 --> 00:43:58,040
 We ask in Jesus' name.

750
00:43:58,040 --> 00:43:58,540
 Amen.

